cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.SD 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on clustering a lexicon of words. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses machine learning techniques such as spectral clustering and compares its performance with other clustering methods, indicating a possible fit with cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also evaluates the resulting clusters by using them as features for solving two classical NLP tasks, which suggests a possible fit with cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper deals with statistical language processing, indicating a possible fit with cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with clustering, which suggests a possible fit with cs.SD (Software Development).
